- Prefer simpler explanations with fewer assumptions
- Natural explanations over supernatural ones
- Known entities over invented ones
- "Unknown natural" always better than "supernatural mind"

### Methodological Naturalism
- Only natural things confirmed through reliable methodology
- Science is the only method that consistently separates real from imaginary
- Deference to scientific consensus

### Nominalism Applied
- Don't assume concepts are real things without demonstration
- Properties are linguistic shortcuts, not entities
